st?\n\nTry Our Weather API\n\nWeather API Globe\n\n## Calidad del aire\n\nDatos completos\n\n0\n\n19\n\n500\n\nCalidad del aire: Buena\n\n## Índice de polen\n\nDatos completos\n\nÁrbol\n\n0 / 5\n\n0 1 2 3 4 5\n\nHierba\n\n0 / 5\n\n0 1 2 3 4 5\n\nCésped\n\n0 / 5\n\n0 1 2 3 4 5\n\n## Resumen del tiempo de hoy\n\nDía siguiente\n\nEl tiempo en Goicoechea el domingo, 14 de junio: Lluvias por la mañana, durante el resto del día nubes.\n\n### Previsión meteorológica para Goicoechea el domingo, 14 de junio:\n\nLa temperatura máxima del día será de 85°F a las 3 pm, mientras que la temperatura mínima será de 73°F a las 2 am.\nSe espera un día extremadamente húmedo , con una humedad relativa del 91% que podría variar del 72% hasta un máximo del 100% a las 5 am. Se prevé viento leve de componente este, que podrá llegar a los 7 mph a las 10 am. La proporción de nubes será del 100 %.\n\nLa probabilidad de precipitación puede variar durante el día entre el 0% y el 45% . El momento del día con mayor probabilidad de precipitación será alrededor de las 11 am y la hora con menor probabilidad, las 12 am. El punto de condensación podría variar desde los 73°F hasta los 78°F alrededor de las 12 pm.\n\nLa visibilidad será media , con un grado de visibilidad de 6 mi a lo largo del día. Se espera una presión atmosférica media y la presión media será de 1013 hPa. El sol saldrá a las 5:15 am y la puesta del sol será alrededor de las 6:00 pm. El día tendrá 12 horas y 45 minutos de luz solar.\n\n### Previsión de la calidad del aire en Goicoechea el domingo 14 de junio:\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9962e2304e0073b8\">>>","siteName":"weather.tomorrow.io","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fa6a41202f765d6c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nClima en Goicoechea Hoy — Pronóstico del Tiempo por Hora ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fa6a41202f765d6c\">>>","url":"https://acontecer.co.cr/clima/san-jose/goicoechea","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2e085ce2d4f555f1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSaltar al contenido principal\n\nInicio › Clima › San José › Goicoechea\n\nServicio en vivo · Open-Meteo\n\n# Clima en Goicoechea hoy\n\nPronóstico del tiempo en Goicoechea, San José: temperatura actual, por hora y de 7 días. La información se actualiza automáticamente cada 30 minutos.\n\n☁️\n\nGoicoechea · ahora\n\n24 °C\n\nNublado\n\nSensación 25°C\n\nHumedad 65%\n\nViento 8 km/h\n\n## Pronóstico por hora · Goicoechea\n\n08:00 ☁️ 24° 💧 46%\n\n09:00 ⛅ 25° 💧 65%\n\n10:00 🌧️ 24° 💧 76%\n\n11:00 🌧️ 25° 💧 83%\n\n12:00 🌦️ 23° 💧 88%\n\n13:00 🌧️ 22° 💧 90%\n\n14:00 🌦️ 22° 💧 90%\n\n15:00 ☁️ 23° 💧 90%\n\n16:00 ☁️ 23° 💧 92%\n\n17:00 ☁️ 23° 💧 94%\n\n18:00 ☁️ 22° 💧 88%\n\n19:00 ☁️ 22° 💧 68%\n\n20:00 ☁️ 22° 💧 41%\n\n21:00 ☁️ 22° 💧 20%\n\n22:00 ☁️ 21° 💧 11%\n\n23:00 ☁️ 21° 💧 8%\n\n00:00 ☁️ 20° 💧 6%\n\n01:00 ⛅ 20° 💧 3%\n\n02:00 ☁️ 19° 💧 2%\n\n03:00 ☁️ 19° 💧 2%\n\n04:00 ☁️ 18° 💧 3%\n\n05:00 ☁️ 18° 💧 6%\n\n06:00 ☁️ 19° 💧 10%\n\n07:00 🌦️ 21° 💧 16%\n## Pronóstico de 7 días · Goicoechea\n\nHoy 🌧️ **25°** 19° 💧 94%\n\nlun 🌧️ **26°** 18° 💧 98%\n\nmar 🌧️ **25°** 19° 💧 99%\n\nmié 🌧️ **26°** 18° 💧 100%\n\njue 🌧️ **24°** 17° 💧 100%\n\nvie 🌧️ **24°** 17° 💧 100%\n\nsáb 🌧️ **20°** 17° 💧 100%\n\n## El clima en Goicoechea, San José\n\nSan José, en el Valle Central, tiene un clima templado de montaña: días agradables y noches frescas durante todo el año, con lluvias por la tarde en la estación lluviosa.\n\nCosta Rica tiene dos estaciones: la seca (de diciembre a abril) y la lluviosa (de mayo a noviembre). En Goicoechea y el resto de San José, el relieve genera microclimas, por lo que la temperatura y la lluvia pueden variar dentro de la misma zona en un mismo día.\n\n**Importante:** esta página es informativa y los datos provienen de modelos meteorológicos automáticos. Para alertas y avisos oficiales, consulte el Instituto Meteorológico Nacional (IMN) y la Comisión Nacional de Emergencias (CNE).\n\n## Preguntas frecuentes\n\n¿Qué clima hace hoy en Goicoechea?\nAhora en Goicoechea hay 24°C (sensación 25°C), nublado, con 65% de humedad. El pronóstico por hora y de 7 días está más arriba en esta página. ¿Cómo estará el tiempo esta semana en Goicoechea?\n\nEn la sección de pronóstico de 7 días se muestran la temperatura máxima y mínima y la probabilidad de lluvia para cada día en Goicoechea, San José. Los datos se actualizan automáticamente cada 30 minutos. ¿De dónde provienen estos datos del clima?\n\nLos datos provienen de modelos meteorológicos abiertos (Open-Meteo) y se actualizan automáticamente. Para alertas y avisos oficiales, la referencia es el Instituto Meteorológico Nacional (IMN) y la Comisión Nacional de Emergencias (CNE).\n\nActualizado automáticamente con datos meteorológicos de Open-Meteo.\n\nClima en San José · Todo Costa Rica · Tipo de cambio\n\nAcontecer.co.cr\n\nSomos la nueva cara del periodismo en Costa Rica. Informamos con responsabilidad, claridad y oportunidad sobre los temas que más importan.\n\n[](https://facebook.com/Acontecer.co.cr) [](https://whatsapp.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2e085ce2d4f555f1\">>>","siteName":"acontecer.co.cr","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4d0f11443877b046\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPronóstico del tiempo para Goicoechea - precisa y detallada ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4d0f11443877b046\">>>","url":"https://es.meteotrend.com/forecast/district/cr/provincia-de-san-jose/goicoechea/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d18125d9f0d5d9f4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPrecisa y detallada previsión del tiempo en Goicoechea. La temperatura y la humedad del aire, presión, velocidad y dirección del viento, la precipitación, la salida del sol, puesta de sol, salida de la luna, puesta de la luna.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d18125d9f0d5d9f4\">>>","siteName":"es.meteotrend.com","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"838850883f29cc16\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPronóstico del tiempo y condiciones meteorológicas para Goicoechea, Provincia de San José, Costa Rica: The Weather Channel | Weather.com\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"838850883f29cc16\">>>","url":"https://weather.com/es-US/tiempo/hoy/l/20ef64b81da30203b8d5aaf1c520d192897713292f012cc402b8d16ff985fcce","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f0e67a09b079778d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPodemos usar o compartir tus datos con nuestros proveedores de datos. Controla tus datos.\n\n* Revisar todas las configuraciones de privacidad y anuncios\n* Elegir cómo se comparte mi información\n* Derechos de los datos\n\nThe Weather Channel es el pronosticador más preciso del mundo según ForecastWatch, [Vista general de la precisión del pronóstico meteorológico mundial y regional](https://forecastwatch.com/AccuracyOverview2021-2024) , 2021-2024, encargado por The Weather Company .\n\nWeather Channel\n\n© The Weather Company, LLC 2026\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f0e67a09b079778d\">>>","siteName":"weather.com","published":"2026-06-14","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ee7b1203e8ae5854\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPronóstico meteorológico de Goicoechea, San-Jose - MSN\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ee7b1203e8ae5854\">>>","url":"https://www.msn.com/es-xl/el-tiempo/pronostico/in-Goicoechea%2CSan-Jose","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"be212642dcfe28a6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPronóstico meteorológico de Goicoechea, San-Jose - MSN\nObtén predicciones precisas por hora para hoy, esta noche y mañana, junto con las predicciones diarias de 10 días y el radar meteorológico en Goicoechea, San-Jose con MSN El Tiempo.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"be212642dcfe28a6\">>>","siteName":"www.msn.com","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}}],"searchId":"search_c098b0b1900c45e1aa1692e3cdb66030","sessionId":"e40865dd-ff0b-4232-b0a9-c4673e966985","usage":[{"name":"sku_search","count":1}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781712086528},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora voy a buscar noticias técnicas para IA Engineers:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8d36d089d19946dc8f6ba19c","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"JavaScript TypeScript AI libraries frameworks 2026 developer tools frontend AI integration tutorials React Vue","freshness":"week","count":5},"partialArgs":"{\"query\": \"JavaScript TypeScript AI libraries frameworks 2026 developer tools frontend AI integration tutorials React Vue\", \"freshness\": \"week\", \"count\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781712086538,"responseId":"gen-1781712086-hkXQ3c7B9fPSMsbLwX9h"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8d36d089d19946dc8f6ba19c","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"searchQueries\": [\n    \"JavaScript TypeScript AI libraries frameworks 2026 developer tools frontend AI integration tutorials React Vue\"\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1938,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"de82ee8c496f26f1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTop JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands-On Comparison | Xavier Portilla Edo\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"de82ee8c496f26f1\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://xavidop.me/genkit/2026-04-16-top-jsts-genai-frameworks-2026\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"103d77739048f6db\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nJump to:\\n\\nNavigation\\n\\n* home\\n* / genkit\\n* / 2026-04-16-top-jsts-genai-frameworks-2026\\n\\n# Top JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands-On Comparison\\n\\n16 Apr 2026 in Genkit on Genkit Last modified at: 2026-05-06\\n\\nTop JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands-On Comparison\\n\\nA practical, in-depth comparison of the top Generative AI frameworks in 2026: Genkit, Vercel AI SDK, Mastra, LangChain, and Google ADK, from someone who has built with all of them. (English)\\n\\n1. Introduction\\n2. Genkit\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. What Makes Genkit Stand Out\\n          \\n        1. Flows — Composable, Typed Pipelines\\n        2. Agent Abstractions\\n        3. The Dev UI — Where Genkit Truly Shines\\n        4. Broad Model Support — Provider Neutral by Design\\n        5. Pros and Cons\\n3. Vercel AI SDK\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. What Makes the Vercel AI SDK Stand Out\\n          \\n        1. Structured Generation and Agent Patterns\\n        2. Genkit vs.\\nVercel AI SDK — Abstraction Levels\\n        3. Pros and Cons\\n4. Mastra\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. What Makes Mastra Stand Out\\n          \\n        1. Workflows\\n        2. Pros and Cons\\n5. LangChain\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. LangChain’s Position: Agent-First, Platform-Tied\\n          \\n        1. LangSmith Observability\\n        2. Pros and Cons\\n6. Google ADK (Agent Development Kit)\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. ADK’s Position: Agent-First, Enterprise-Grade\\n          \\n        1. Multi-Agent Systems\\n        2. Vertex AI Lock-In\\n        3. Pros and Cons\\n7. Head-to-Head Comparison\\n   \\n    1. Developer Experience\\n    2. Abstraction Levels\\n    3. Observability\\n    4. Language Support\\n    5. Framework Neutrality\\n    6. Idiom and Code Style\\n8. Which Framework Should You Choose?\\n9. Conclusion\\n\\n## Introduction\\n\\nThe Generative AI tooling ecosystem has exploded over the past two years.\\nWhat started as a handful of Python libraries has grown into a rich, opinionated landscape of frameworks spanning multiple languages, deployment targets, and philosophy bets. As a developer who has shipped production applications using all five of the frameworks covered in this article, **Genkit** , **Vercel AI SDK** , **Mastra** , **LangChain** , and **Google ADK** , I want to offer a practical, hands-on view of where each one excels, where each one falls short, and what I would reach for depending on the project I’m building.\\n\\nThis is not a benchmark post. Tokens per second and latency numbers go stale within weeks. Instead, this is a developer experience and architecture comparison, the kind of thing that matters when you’re deciding what framework will carry your product through 2026 and beyond.\\n\\nA quick note on scope: all five frameworks are in active development and moving fast. Code samples in this article use the APIs as of **April 2026** .\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## Genkit\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"103d77739048f6db\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"xavidop.me\",\n      \"published\": \"2026-05-06\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"103d77739048f6db\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nJump to:\\n\\nNavigation\\n\\n* home\\n* / genkit\\n* / 2026-04-16-top-jsts-genai-frameworks-2026\\n\\n# Top JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands-On Comparison\\n\\n16 Apr 2026 in Genkit on Genkit Last modified at: 2026-05-06\\n\\nTop JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands-On Comparison\\n\\nA practical, in-depth comparison of the top Generative AI frameworks in 2026: Genkit, Vercel AI SDK, Mastra, LangChain, and Google ADK, from someone who has built with all of them. (English)\\n\\n1. Introduction\\n2. Genkit\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. What Makes Genkit Stand Out\\n          \\n        1. Flows — Composable, Typed Pipelines\\n        2. Agent Abstractions\\n        3. The Dev UI — Where Genkit Truly Shines\\n        4. Broad Model Support — Provider Neutral by Design\\n        5. Pros and Cons\\n3. Vercel AI SDK\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. What Makes the Vercel AI SDK Stand Out\\n          \\n        1. Structured Generation and Agent Patterns\\n        2. Genkit vs.\\nVercel AI SDK — Abstraction Levels\\n        3. Pros and Cons\\n4. Mastra\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. What Makes Mastra Stand Out\\n          \\n        1. Workflows\\n        2. Pros and Cons\\n5. LangChain\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. LangChain’s Position: Agent-First, Platform-Tied\\n          \\n        1. LangSmith Observability\\n        2. Pros and Cons\\n6. Google ADK (Agent Development Kit)\\n   \\n    1. History and Direction\\n    2. ADK’s Position: Agent-First, Enterprise-Grade\\n          \\n        1. Multi-Agent Systems\\n        2. Vertex AI Lock-In\\n        3. Pros and Cons\\n7. Head-to-Head Comparison\\n   \\n    1. Developer Experience\\n    2. Abstraction Levels\\n    3. Observability\\n    4. Language Support\\n    5. Framework Neutrality\\n    6. Idiom and Code Style\\n8. Which Framework Should You Choose?\\n9. Conclusion\\n\\n## Introduction\\n\\nThe Generative AI tooling ecosystem has exploded over the past two years.\\nWhat started as a handful of Python libraries has grown into a rich, opinionated landscape of frameworks spanning multiple languages, deployment targets, and philosophy bets. As a developer who has shipped production applications using all five of the frameworks covered in this article, **Genkit** , **Vercel AI SDK** , **Mastra** , **LangChain** , and **Google ADK** , I want to offer a practical, hands-on view of where each one excels, where each one falls short, and what I would reach for depending on the project I’m building.\\n\\nThis is not a benchmark post. Tokens per second and latency numbers go stale within weeks. Instead, this is a developer experience and architecture comparison, the kind of thing that matters when you’re deciding what framework will carry your product through 2026 and beyond.\\n\\nA quick note on scope: all five frameworks are in active development and moving fast. Code samples in this article use the APIs as of **April 2026** .\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## Genkit\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"103d77739048f6db\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6a4f54eedfc50f2d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTypeScript AI SDKs Rise in 2026: Framework Guide\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6a4f54eedfc50f2d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://marioottmann.com/articles/typescript-ai-sdks-rise-2026\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e86e36f0491b49f5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMario Ottmann\\n\\nArticles Newsletter Presentations [Work with me](https://withGravitas.de)\\n\\nDECEMBER 5, 2025\\n\\n# Why TypeScript-Based AI SDKs Are Reshaping Development in 2026\\n\\ntl;dr\\n\\nTypeScript-based AI SDKs are becoming viable alternatives to Python frameworks in 2026, driven by developers seeking unified tech stacks. While Python remains dominant for computationally intensive tasks, TypeScript frameworks like Mastra excel at orchestration, user-facing AI features, and seamless integration with modern web stacks.\\n\\nThe AI development landscape is undergoing a significant shift. For years, Python has dominated AI SDK adoption through frameworks like LangChain and CrewAI, largely because no competitive TypeScript alternatives existed. However, 2026 marks a turning point as non-technical entrepreneurs and solopreneurs increasingly prioritize unified development stacks over specialized, fragmented solutions.\\nThis evolution reflects a broader trend: developers want to build AI-powered features as native components of their applications, not isolated systems requiring separate environments, deployment pipelines, and expertise. This article was inspired by real-world experiences navigating this transition. Here's the LinkedIn post that sparked this comprehensive guide:\\n\\n## What Are TypeScript-Based AI SDKs?\\n\\nTypeScript-based AI SDKs are development frameworks that enable building AI-powered applications using TypeScript, JavaScript's statically-typed superset. Unlike traditional Python-centric AI tools, these SDKs integrate natively with modern web development stacks (React, Next.js, Node.js), allowing developers to build AI features using the same language and toolchain as their frontend and backend code. This unified approach eliminates context-switching and simplifies deployment architectures.\\nThese frameworks provide type-safe interfaces for interacting with large language models (LLMs), vector databases, agent orchestration systems, and other AI infrastructure. They're designed for developers who prioritize rapid iteration, seamless integration, and developer experience over raw computational performance.\\n\\n### The Historical Context: Python's Dominance\\n\\nPython became the default choice for AI development for legitimate reasons:\\n\\n* **Rich ecosystem** : Mature libraries like NumPy, pandas, and scikit-learn\\n* **Academic adoption** : Most AI research published with Python implementations\\n* **Framework maturity** : Early frameworks like LangChain and Crew AI launched Python-first\\n* **Community momentum** : Largest concentration of AI practitioners and resources\\n\\nHowever, this dominance created friction for web developers building AI-powered applications.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e86e36f0491b49f5\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"marioottmann.com\",\n      \"published\": \"2025-12-05\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e86e36f0491b49f5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMario Ottmann\\n\\nArticles Newsletter Presentations [Work with me](https://withGravitas.de)\\n\\nDECEMBER 5, 2025\\n\\n# Why TypeScript-Based AI SDKs Are Reshaping Development in 2026\\n\\ntl;dr\\n\\nTypeScript-based AI SDKs are becoming viable alternatives to Python frameworks in 2026, driven by developers seeking unified tech stacks. While Python remains dominant for computationally intensive tasks, TypeScript frameworks like Mastra excel at orchestration, user-facing AI features, and seamless integration with modern web stacks.\\n\\nThe AI development landscape is undergoing a significant shift. For years, Python has dominated AI SDK adoption through frameworks like LangChain and CrewAI, largely because no competitive TypeScript alternatives existed. However, 2026 marks a turning point as non-technical entrepreneurs and solopreneurs increasingly prioritize unified development stacks over specialized, fragmented solutions.\\nThis evolution reflects a broader trend: developers want to build AI-powered features as native components of their applications, not isolated systems requiring separate environments, deployment pipelines, and expertise. This article was inspired by real-world experiences navigating this transition. Here's the LinkedIn post that sparked this comprehensive guide:\\n\\n## What Are TypeScript-Based AI SDKs?\\n\\nTypeScript-based AI SDKs are development frameworks that enable building AI-powered applications using TypeScript, JavaScript's statically-typed superset. Unlike traditional Python-centric AI tools, these SDKs integrate natively with modern web development stacks (React, Next.js, Node.js), allowing developers to build AI features using the same language and toolchain as their frontend and backend code. This unified approach eliminates context-switching and simplifies deployment architectures.\\nThese frameworks provide type-safe interfaces for interacting with large language models (LLMs), vector databases, agent orchestration systems, and other AI infrastructure. They're designed for developers who prioritize rapid iteration, seamless integration, and developer experience over raw computational performance.\\n\\n### The Historical Context: Python's Dominance\\n\\nPython became the default choice for AI development for legitimate reasons:\\n\\n* **Rich ecosystem** : Mature libraries like NumPy, pandas, and scikit-learn\\n* **Academic adoption** : Most AI research published with Python implementations\\n* **Framework maturity** : Early frameworks like LangChain and Crew AI launched Python-first\\n* **Community momentum** : Largest concentration of AI practitioners and resources\\n\\nHowever, this dominance created friction for web developers building AI-powered applications.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e86e36f0491b49f5\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7dac898f59418c1a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFrontend Development Trends 2026: AI, Edge & TypeScript\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7dac898f59418c1a\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://talent500.com/blog/frontend-development-trends-2026/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7cabe46dad6aaf9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDiscover the key trends that will shape frontend development in 2026, from AI-first workflows and meta-frameworks to edge computing, TypeScript, and modern frontend architecture.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7cabe46dad6aaf9\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"talent500.com\",\n      \"published\": \"2026-01-23\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7cabe46dad6aaf9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDiscover the key trends that will shape frontend development in 2026, from AI-first workflows and meta-frameworks to edge computing, TypeScript, and modern frontend architecture.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7cabe46dad6aaf9\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4c56e5215eb944d3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTop JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4c56e5215eb944d3\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://dev.to/gde/top-javascripttypescript-gen-ai-frameworks-for-2026-a-hands-on-comparisondescription-1g7\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7e098a3963afb103\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe Generative AI framework landscape in 2026 is not a winner-take-all market. Each of the five frameworks covered here has a legitimate use case, a growing community, and an active development team.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7e098a3963afb103\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"dev.to\",\n      \"published\": \"2026-05-05\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7e098a3963afb103\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe Generative AI framework landscape in 2026 is not a winner-take-all market. Each of the five frameworks covered here has a legitimate use case, a growing community, and an active development team.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7e098a3963afb103\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"579bdb8948f2f70c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTypeScript Agent Frameworks in 2026: Loop, Runtime, Sandbox - DEV Community\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"579bdb8948f2f70c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://dev.to/joeseifi/typescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"825f431ff53a6af5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Powered by Algolia](https://www.algolia.com/developers/?utm_source=devto&utm_medium=referral)\\n\\n \\n\\n## DEV Community\\n\\nAdd reaction\\n\\nLike Unicorn Exploding Head Raised Hands Fire\\n\\nJump to Comments Save Boost\\n\\nCopy link\\n\\nCopied to Clipboard\\n\\n[Share to X](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=%22TypeScript%20Agent%20Frameworks%20in%202026%3A%20Loop%2C%20Runtime%2C%20Sandbox%22%20by%20%40joeseifi%20%23DEVCommunity%20https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm) [Share to LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm&title=TypeScript%20Agent%20Frameworks%20in%202026%3A%20Loop%2C%20Runtime%2C%20Sandbox&summary=A%20working%20senior%20engineer%27s%20map%20of%20TypeScript%20AI%20agent%20frameworks%20across%20three%20layers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20loop%2C%20the%20runtime%2C%20and%20the%20sandbox.%20Most%20teams%20need%20none%20of%20them.\\n&source=DEV%20Community) [Share to Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm) [Share to Mastodon](https://s2f.kytta.dev/?text=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm)\\n\\nReport Abuse\\n\\n[](https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=1000,height=420,fit=cover,gravity=auto,format=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2F49n2hz3zsxd3vsakf2r1.png)\\n\\nJoe Seifi\\n\\nPosted on May 3 • Originally published at [everydev.ai](https://everydev.ai/p/blog-typescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox)\\n\\n# TypeScript Agent Frameworks in 2026: Loop, Runtime, Sandbox\\n\\n\\\\# typescript \\\\# ai \\\\# agents \\\\# frameworks\\n\\n[](https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2F49n2hz3zsxd3vsakf2r1.png)\\nMost TypeScript teams shopping for an agent framework don't need one. A single `generateObject` call covers classification, extraction, summarization, tagging — the 80% case for production LLM work in TS right now.\\n\\nBut once the model starts deciding what to do next, surviving deploys, or coordinating with other agents, you start shopping. And the moment you do, you discover the TS agent ecosystem is not one market but three.\\n\\n##  Three layers\\n\\n**Loop** — wraps the agent loop so you don't write `while (!done) {…}` yourself. \\\"Let the model decide what to do next.\\\"\\n\\nMastra, Vercel AI SDK, Claude Agent SDK, OpenAI Agents SDK, LangGraph, AgentKit, VoltAgent, Google ADK.\\n\\n**Runtime** — keeps the loop alive across crashes, deploys, and long pauses. \\\"Keep the work alive when servers die.\\\"\\n\\nMastra Platform, LangGraph Platform, Claude Managed Agents, Inngest, Flue.\\n\\n**Sandbox** — runs an existing coding agent in isolation, often in parallel. \\\"Run ten Claude Codes in ten boxes.\\\"\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"825f431ff53a6af5\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"dev.to\",\n      \"published\": \"2026-05-03\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"825f431ff53a6af5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Powered by Algolia](https://www.algolia.com/developers/?utm_source=devto&utm_medium=referral)\\n\\n \\n\\n## DEV Community\\n\\nAdd reaction\\n\\nLike Unicorn Exploding Head Raised Hands Fire\\n\\nJump to Comments Save Boost\\n\\nCopy link\\n\\nCopied to Clipboard\\n\\n[Share to X](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=%22TypeScript%20Agent%20Frameworks%20in%202026%3A%20Loop%2C%20Runtime%2C%20Sandbox%22%20by%20%40joeseifi%20%23DEVCommunity%20https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm) [Share to LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm&title=TypeScript%20Agent%20Frameworks%20in%202026%3A%20Loop%2C%20Runtime%2C%20Sandbox&summary=A%20working%20senior%20engineer%27s%20map%20of%20TypeScript%20AI%20agent%20frameworks%20across%20three%20layers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20loop%2C%20the%20runtime%2C%20and%20the%20sandbox.%20Most%20teams%20need%20none%20of%20them.\\n&source=DEV%20Community) [Share to Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm) [Share to Mastodon](https://s2f.kytta.dev/?text=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm)\\n\\nReport Abuse\\n\\n[](https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=1000,height=420,fit=cover,gravity=auto,format=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2F49n2hz3zsxd3vsakf2r1.png)\\n\\nJoe Seifi\\n\\nPosted on May 3 • Originally published at [everydev.ai](https://everydev.ai/p/blog-typescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox)\\n\\n# TypeScript Agent Frameworks in 2026: Loop, Runtime, Sandbox\\n\\n\\\\# typescript \\\\# ai \\\\# agents \\\\# frameworks\\n\\n[](https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2F49n2hz3zsxd3vsakf2r1.png)\\nMost TypeScript teams shopping for an agent framework don't need one. A single `generateObject` call covers classification, extraction, summarization, tagging — the 80% case for production LLM work in TS right now.\\n\\nBut once the model starts deciding what to do next, surviving deploys, or coordinating with other agents, you start shopping. And the moment you do, you discover the TS agent ecosystem is not one market but three.\\n\\n##  Three layers\\n\\n**Loop** — wraps the agent loop so you don't write `while (!done) {…}` yourself. \\\"Let the model decide what to do next.\\\"\\n\\nMastra, Vercel AI SDK, Claude Agent SDK, OpenAI Agents SDK, LangGraph, AgentKit, VoltAgent, Google ADK.\\n\\n**Runtime** — keeps the loop alive across crashes, deploys, and long pauses. \\\"Keep the work alive when servers die.\\\"\\n\\nMastra Platform, LangGraph Platform, Claude Managed Agents, Inngest, Flue.\\n\\n**Sandbox** — runs an existing coding agent in isolation, often in parallel. \\\"Run ten Claude Codes in ten boxes.\\\"\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"825f431ff53a6af5\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"searchId\": \"search_9a2dec32cb09475094600643c52ab62f\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"a41f975a-4880-459f-ab8f-7001c9813408\",\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"searchQueries":["JavaScript TypeScript AI libraries frameworks 2026 developer tools frontend AI integration tutorials React Vue"],"provider":"parallel-free","count":5,"tookMs":1938,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"parallel-free","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"de82ee8c496f26f1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTop JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands-On Comparison | Xavier Portilla Edo\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"de82ee8c496f26f1\">>>","url":"https://xavidop.me/genkit/2026-04-16-top-jsts-genai-frameworks-2026","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"103d77739048f6db\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nJump to:\n\nNavigation\n\n* home\n* / genkit\n* / 2026-04-16-top-jsts-genai-frameworks-2026\n\n# Top JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands-On Comparison\n\n16 Apr 2026 in Genkit on Genkit Last modified at: 2026-05-06\n\nTop JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands-On Comparison\n\nA practical, in-depth comparison of the top Generative AI frameworks in 2026: Genkit, Vercel AI SDK, Mastra, LangChain, and Google ADK, from someone who has built with all of them. (English)\n\n1. Introduction\n2. Genkit\n   \n    1. History and Direction\n    2. What Makes Genkit Stand Out\n          \n        1. Flows — Composable, Typed Pipelines\n        2. Agent Abstractions\n        3. The Dev UI — Where Genkit Truly Shines\n        4. Broad Model Support — Provider Neutral by Design\n        5. Pros and Cons\n3. Vercel AI SDK\n   \n    1. History and Direction\n    2. What Makes the Vercel AI SDK Stand Out\n          \n        1. Structured Generation and Agent Patterns\n        2. Genkit vs.\nVercel AI SDK — Abstraction Levels\n        3. Pros and Cons\n4. Mastra\n   \n    1. History and Direction\n    2. What Makes Mastra Stand Out\n          \n        1. Workflows\n        2. Pros and Cons\n5. LangChain\n   \n    1. History and Direction\n    2. LangChain’s Position: Agent-First, Platform-Tied\n          \n        1. LangSmith Observability\n        2. Pros and Cons\n6. Google ADK (Agent Development Kit)\n   \n    1. History and Direction\n    2. ADK’s Position: Agent-First, Enterprise-Grade\n          \n        1. Multi-Agent Systems\n        2. Vertex AI Lock-In\n        3. Pros and Cons\n7. Head-to-Head Comparison\n   \n    1. Developer Experience\n    2. Abstraction Levels\n    3. Observability\n    4. Language Support\n    5. Framework Neutrality\n    6. Idiom and Code Style\n8. Which Framework Should You Choose?\n9. Conclusion\n\n## Introduction\n\nThe Generative AI tooling ecosystem has exploded over the past two years.\nWhat started as a handful of Python libraries has grown into a rich, opinionated landscape of frameworks spanning multiple languages, deployment targets, and philosophy bets. As a developer who has shipped production applications using all five of the frameworks covered in this article, **Genkit** , **Vercel AI SDK** , **Mastra** , **LangChain** , and **Google ADK** , I want to offer a practical, hands-on view of where each one excels, where each one falls short, and what I would reach for depending on the project I’m building.\n\nThis is not a benchmark post. Tokens per second and latency numbers go stale within weeks. Instead, this is a developer experience and architecture comparison, the kind of thing that matters when you’re deciding what framework will carry your product through 2026 and beyond.\n\nA quick note on scope: all five frameworks are in active development and moving fast. Code samples in this article use the APIs as of **April 2026** .\n\n* * *\n\n## Genkit\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"103d77739048f6db\">>>","siteName":"xavidop.me","published":"2026-05-06","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6a4f54eedfc50f2d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTypeScript AI SDKs Rise in 2026: Framework Guide\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6a4f54eedfc50f2d\">>>","url":"https://marioottmann.com/articles/typescript-ai-sdks-rise-2026","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e86e36f0491b49f5\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMario Ottmann\n\nArticles Newsletter Presentations [Work with me](https://withGravitas.de)\n\nDECEMBER 5, 2025\n\n# Why TypeScript-Based AI SDKs Are Reshaping Development in 2026\n\ntl;dr\n\nTypeScript-based AI SDKs are becoming viable alternatives to Python frameworks in 2026, driven by developers seeking unified tech stacks. While Python remains dominant for computationally intensive tasks, TypeScript frameworks like Mastra excel at orchestration, user-facing AI features, and seamless integration with modern web stacks.\n\nThe AI development landscape is undergoing a significant shift. For years, Python has dominated AI SDK adoption through frameworks like LangChain and CrewAI, largely because no competitive TypeScript alternatives existed. However, 2026 marks a turning point as non-technical entrepreneurs and solopreneurs increasingly prioritize unified development stacks over specialized, fragmented solutions.\nThis evolution reflects a broader trend: developers want to build AI-powered features as native components of their applications, not isolated systems requiring separate environments, deployment pipelines, and expertise. This article was inspired by real-world experiences navigating this transition. Here's the LinkedIn post that sparked this comprehensive guide:\n\n## What Are TypeScript-Based AI SDKs?\n\nTypeScript-based AI SDKs are development frameworks that enable building AI-powered applications using TypeScript, JavaScript's statically-typed superset. Unlike traditional Python-centric AI tools, these SDKs integrate natively with modern web development stacks (React, Next.js, Node.js), allowing developers to build AI features using the same language and toolchain as their frontend and backend code. This unified approach eliminates context-switching and simplifies deployment architectures.\nThese frameworks provide type-safe interfaces for interacting with large language models (LLMs), vector databases, agent orchestration systems, and other AI infrastructure. They're designed for developers who prioritize rapid iteration, seamless integration, and developer experience over raw computational performance.\n\n### The Historical Context: Python's Dominance\n\nPython became the default choice for AI development for legitimate reasons:\n\n* **Rich ecosystem** : Mature libraries like NumPy, pandas, and scikit-learn\n* **Academic adoption** : Most AI research published with Python implementations\n* **Framework maturity** : Early frameworks like LangChain and Crew AI launched Python-first\n* **Community momentum** : Largest concentration of AI practitioners and resources\n\nHowever, this dominance created friction for web developers building AI-powered applications.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e86e36f0491b49f5\">>>","siteName":"marioottmann.com","published":"2025-12-05","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7dac898f59418c1a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFrontend Development Trends 2026: AI, Edge & TypeScript\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7dac898f59418c1a\">>>","url":"https://talent500.com/blog/frontend-development-trends-2026/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b7cabe46dad6aaf9\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nDiscover the key trends that will shape frontend development in 2026, from AI-first workflows and meta-frameworks to edge computing, TypeScript, and modern frontend architecture.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b7cabe46dad6aaf9\">>>","siteName":"talent500.com","published":"2026-01-23","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4c56e5215eb944d3\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTop JavaScript/TypeScript Gen AI Frameworks for 2026: A Hands ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4c56e5215eb944d3\">>>","url":"https://dev.to/gde/top-javascripttypescript-gen-ai-frameworks-for-2026-a-hands-on-comparisondescription-1g7","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7e098a3963afb103\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe Generative AI framework landscape in 2026 is not a winner-take-all market. Each of the five frameworks covered here has a legitimate use case, a growing community, and an active development team.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7e098a3963afb103\">>>","siteName":"dev.to","published":"2026-05-05","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"579bdb8948f2f70c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTypeScript Agent Frameworks in 2026: Loop, Runtime, Sandbox - DEV Community\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"579bdb8948f2f70c\">>>","url":"https://dev.to/joeseifi/typescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"825f431ff53a6af5\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[Powered by Algolia](https://www.algolia.com/developers/?utm_source=devto&utm_medium=referral)\n\n \n\n## DEV Community\n\nAdd reaction\n\nLike Unicorn Exploding Head Raised Hands Fire\n\nJump to Comments Save Boost\n\nCopy link\n\nCopied to Clipboard\n\n[Share to X](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=%22TypeScript%20Agent%20Frameworks%20in%202026%3A%20Loop%2C%20Runtime%2C%20Sandbox%22%20by%20%40joeseifi%20%23DEVCommunity%20https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm) [Share to LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm&title=TypeScript%20Agent%20Frameworks%20in%202026%3A%20Loop%2C%20Runtime%2C%20Sandbox&summary=<redacted>\n&source=DEV%20Community) [Share to Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm) [Share to Mastodon](https://s2f.kytta.dev/?text=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.to%2Fjoeseifi%2Ftypescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox-2flm)\n\nReport Abuse\n\n[](https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=1000,height=420,fit=cover,gravity=auto,format=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2F49n2hz3zsxd3vsakf2r1.png)\n\nJoe Seifi\n\nPosted on May 3 • Originally published at [everydev.ai](https://everydev.ai/p/blog-typescript-agent-frameworks-in-2026-loop-runtime-sandbox)\n\n# TypeScript Agent Frameworks in 2026: Loop, Runtime, Sandbox\n\n\\# typescript \\# ai \\# agents \\# frameworks\n\n[](https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2F49n2hz3zsxd3vsakf2r1.png)\nMost TypeScript teams shopping for an agent framework don't need one. A single `generateObject` call covers classification, extraction, summarization, tagging — the 80% case for production LLM work in TS right now.\n\nBut once the model starts deciding what to do next, surviving deploys, or coordinating with other agents, you start shopping. And the moment you do, you discover the TS agent ecosystem is not one market but three.\n\n##  Three layers\n\n**Loop** — wraps the agent loop so you don't write `while (!done) {…}` yourself. \"Let the model decide what to do next.\"\n\nMastra, Vercel AI SDK, Claude Agent SDK, OpenAI Agents SDK, LangGraph, AgentKit, VoltAgent, Google ADK.\n\n**Runtime** — keeps the loop alive across crashes, deploys, and long pauses. \"Keep the work alive when servers die.\"\n\nMastra Platform, LangGraph Platform, Claude Managed Agents, Inngest, Flue.\n\n**Sandbox** — runs an existing coding agent in isolation, often in parallel. \"Run ten Claude Codes in ten boxes.\"\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"825f431ff53a6af5\">>>","siteName":"dev.to","published":"2026-05-03","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}}],"searchId":"search_9a2dec32cb09475094600643c52ab62f","sessionId":"a41f975a-4880-459f-ab8f-7001c9813408","usage":[{"name":"sku_search","count":1}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781712111325},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora voy a buscar más información específica sobre aprendizaje práctico de IA:\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"3a62eaf6a7ed4f788dc4e1a91472969a","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"AI engineering learning resources tutorials projects 2026 React TypeScript practical applications","freshness":"month","count":3},"partialArgs":"{\"query\": \"AI engineering learning resources tutorials projects 2026 React TypeScript practical applications\", \"freshness\": \"month\", \"count\": 3}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781712111335,"responseId":"gen-1781712111-rEPwnqFsp5cJTpsyHsju"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"3a62eaf6a7ed4f788dc4e1a91472969a","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"searchQueries\": [\n    \"AI engineering learning resources tutorials projects 2026 React TypeScript practical applications\"\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n  \"count\": 3,\n  \"tookMs\": 3330,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"90e0e3d1d4e23a92\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Learning Decoded: The Courses, Repos, and Resources ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"90e0e3d1d4e23a92\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://tutorialsearch.io/blog/ai-learning-decoded-courses-repos-resources-worth-your-time-2026\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"156c54391ddf1b63\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Learning Decoded: The Courses, Repos, and Resources ...\\nA curated, honest guide to the best AI learning resources in 2026 — paid courses, free tutorials, GitHub repos, YouTube channels, books, and communities, ranked by someone who actually tested them.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"156c54391ddf1b63\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"tutorialsearch.io\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"156c54391ddf1b63\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Learning Decoded: The Courses, Repos, and Resources ...\\nA curated, honest guide to the best AI learning resources in 2026 — paid courses, free tutorials, GitHub repos, YouTube channels, books, and communities, ranked by someone who actually tested them.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"156c54391ddf1b63\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b08d5d425e1cd618\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Engineering from Scratch\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b08d5d425e1cd618\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://aiengineeringfromscratch.com/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f50fd97d847ee415\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI / FROM SCRATCH\\n\\nContents Catalog Roadmap Glossary About […](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch)\\n\\nN\\n\\nFIG\\\\_000 · curriculum v1.0 · 2026 open source · MIT\\n\\n# AI Engineering  \\nfrom Scratch\\n\\n503 lessons. 20 phases. Every algorithm built from raw math before a single framework gets imported.\\n\\nMaintained by Rohit Ghumare and contributors. Run on your own machine.\\n\\n[Star on GitHub …](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) [Follow @rohitg00](https://github.com/rohitg00)\\n\\nHow this works\\n\\nMost AI material teaches in scattered pieces. A paper here, a fine-tuning post there, a flashy agent demo somewhere else. The pieces rarely line up. You ship a chatbot but can't explain its loss curve. You hook a function to an agent but can't say what attention does inside the model that's calling it.\\n\\nThis curriculum is the spine. 20 phases, 503 lessons, four languages: Python, TypeScript, Rust, Julia. Linear algebra at one end, autonomous swarms at the other. Every algorithm gets built from raw math first. Backprop. Tokenizer. Attention. Agent loop. By the time PyTorch shows up, you already know what it's doing under the hood.\\n\\nEach lesson runs the same loop: read the problem, derive the math, write the code, run the test, keep the artifact. No five-minute videos, no copy-paste deploys, no hand-holding. Free, open source, and built to run on your own laptop.\\n\\nCurrent Progress\\n\\nFinished Lessons bar 0 / 0\\n\\nPhases bar 0 / 0\\n\\nLanguages bar 4\\n\\nGlossary Terms bar ···\\n\\nCurriculum · 20 phases · 503 lessons\\n\\nTap a phase to expand its lessons. Each one ships when its math, code, and test are all written.\\n\\nComplete In progress Planned\\n\\n×\\n\\nProgress saved in browser only Reset progress\\n\\nColophon\\n\\nThe entire curriculum is on GitHub. Clone it, fork it, learn at your own pace. No paywall, no signup. Every lesson has runnable code in Python, TypeScript, Rust, or Julia, depending on what fits the concept best.\\n\\n`git clone https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch.git` cp\\n\\n[GitHub](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) About Catalog Glossary [Report](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch/issues/new/choose)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f50fd97d847ee415\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"aiengineeringfromscratch.com\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f50fd97d847ee415\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI / FROM SCRATCH\\n\\nContents Catalog Roadmap Glossary About […](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch)\\n\\nN\\n\\nFIG\\\\_000 · curriculum v1.0 · 2026 open source · MIT\\n\\n# AI Engineering  \\nfrom Scratch\\n\\n503 lessons. 20 phases. Every algorithm built from raw math before a single framework gets imported.\\n\\nMaintained by Rohit Ghumare and contributors. Run on your own machine.\\n\\n[Star on GitHub …](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) [Follow @rohitg00](https://github.com/rohitg00)\\n\\nHow this works\\n\\nMost AI material teaches in scattered pieces. A paper here, a fine-tuning post there, a flashy agent demo somewhere else. The pieces rarely line up. You ship a chatbot but can't explain its loss curve. You hook a function to an agent but can't say what attention does inside the model that's calling it.\\n\\nThis curriculum is the spine. 20 phases, 503 lessons, four languages: Python, TypeScript, Rust, Julia. Linear algebra at one end, autonomous swarms at the other. Every algorithm gets built from raw math first. Backprop. Tokenizer. Attention. Agent loop. By the time PyTorch shows up, you already know what it's doing under the hood.\\n\\nEach lesson runs the same loop: read the problem, derive the math, write the code, run the test, keep the artifact. No five-minute videos, no copy-paste deploys, no hand-holding. Free, open source, and built to run on your own laptop.\\n\\nCurrent Progress\\n\\nFinished Lessons bar 0 / 0\\n\\nPhases bar 0 / 0\\n\\nLanguages bar 4\\n\\nGlossary Terms bar ···\\n\\nCurriculum · 20 phases · 503 lessons\\n\\nTap a phase to expand its lessons. Each one ships when its math, code, and test are all written.\\n\\nComplete In progress Planned\\n\\n×\\n\\nProgress saved in browser only Reset progress\\n\\nColophon\\n\\nThe entire curriculum is on GitHub. Clone it, fork it, learn at your own pace. No paywall, no signup. Every lesson has runnable code in Python, TypeScript, Rust, or Julia, depending on what fits the concept best.\\n\\n`git clone https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch.git` cp\\n\\n[GitHub](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) About Catalog Glossary [Report](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch/issues/new/choose)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f50fd97d847ee415\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3180cd7f2a1bacdd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - patchy631/ai-engineering-hub: In-depth tutorials on LLMs, RAGs and real-world AI agent applications. · GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3180cd7f2a1bacdd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/patchy631/ai-engineering-hub\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n## Navigation Menu\\n\\nToggle navigation\\n\\nAppearance settings\\n\\nSearch or jump to...\\n\\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests...\\n\\nAppearance settings\\n\\nResetting focus\\n\\npatchy631 / **ai-engineering-hub** Public\\n\\n* Notifications You must be signed in to change notification settings\\n* Fork 5\\\\.9k\\n* Star 35\\\\.4k\\n\\n# patchy631/ai-engineering-hub\\n\\nmain\\n\\nBranches Tags\\n\\n \\n\\nGo to file\\n\\nCode\\n\\nOpen more actions menu\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* MIT license\\n\\n[Trending Badge](https://trendshift.io/repositories/12800)\\n\\nAI Engineering Hub Banner\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n# AI Engineering Hub 🚀\\n\\nWelcome to the **AI Engineering Hub** \\\\- your comprehensive resource for learning and building with AI!\\n\\n## 🌟 Why This Repo?\\n\\nAI Engineering is advancing rapidly, and staying at the forefront requires both deep understanding and hands-on experience. Here, you will find:\\n\\n* **93+ Production-Ready Projects** across all skill levels\\n* In-depth tutorials on **LLMs, RAG, Agents, and more**\\n* Real-world **AI agent** applications\\n* Examples to implement, adapt, and scale in your projects\\n\\nWhether you're a beginner, practitioner, or researcher, this repo provides resources for all skill levels to experiment and succeed in AI engineering.\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 📋 Table of Contents\\n\\n* Getting Started\\n* Newsletter\\n* Projects by Difficulty\\n  \\n    + Beginner Projects (22)\\n    + Intermediate Projects (48)\\n    + Advanced Projects (23)\\n* Contributing\\n* License\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 🎯 Getting Started\\n\\n1. **Complete Beginners** : Check out the AI Engineering Roadmap for a comprehensive learning path\\n2. **Learn the Basics** : Start with Beginner Projects like OCR apps and simple RAG implementations\\n3. **Build Your Skills** : Move to Intermediate Projects with agents and complex workflows\\n4. **Master Advanced Concepts** : Tackle Advanced Projects including fine-tuning and production systems\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 📬 Stay Updated with Our Newsletter!\\n\\n**Get a FREE Data Science eBook** 📖 with 150+ essential lessons in Data Science when you subscribe to our newsletter! Stay in the loop with the latest tutorials, insights, and exclusive resources. [Subscribe now!](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\\n\\n[Daily Dose of Data Science Newsletter](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 🎓 Projects by Difficulty\\n\\n### 🟢 Beginner Projects\\n\\nPerfect for getting started with AI engineering. These projects focus on single components and straightforward implementations.\\n\\n#### OCR & Vision\\n\\n* **LaTeX OCR with Llama** \\\\- Convert LaTeX equation images to code using Llama 3.2 vision\\n* **Llama OCR** \\\\- 100% local OCR app with Llama 3.2 and Streamlit\\n* **Gemma-3 OCR** \\\\- Local OCR with structured text extraction using Gemma-3\\n* **Qwen 2.5 OCR** \\\\- Text extraction using Qwen 2.5 VL model\\n\\n#### Chat Interfaces & UI\\n\\n* **Local ChatGPT with DeepSeek** \\\\- Mini-ChatGPT with DeepSeek-R1 and Chainlit\\n* **Local ChatGPT with Llama** \\\\- ChatGPT clone using Llama 3.2 vision\\n* **Local ChatGPT with Gemma 3** \\\\- Local chat interface with Gemma 3\\n* **DeepSeek \\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n## Navigation Menu\\n\\nToggle navigation\\n\\nAppearance settings\\n\\nSearch or jump to...\\n\\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests...\\n\\nAppearance settings\\n\\nResetting focus\\n\\npatchy631 / **ai-engineering-hub** Public\\n\\n* Notifications You must be signed in to change notification settings\\n* Fork 5\\\\.9k\\n* Star 35\\\\.4k\\n\\n# patchy631/ai-engineering-hub\\n\\nmain\\n\\nBranches Tags\\n\\n \\n\\nGo to file\\n\\nCode\\n\\nOpen more actions menu\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* MIT license\\n\\n[Trending Badge](https://trendshift.io/repositories/12800)\\n\\nAI Engineering Hub Banner\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n# AI Engineering Hub 🚀\\n\\nWelcome to the **AI Engineering Hub** \\\\- your comprehensive resource for learning and building with AI!\\n\\n## 🌟 Why This Repo?\\n\\nAI Engineering is advancing rapidly, and staying at the forefront requires both deep understanding and hands-on experience. Here, you will find:\\n\\n* **93+ Production-Ready Projects** across all skill levels\\n* In-depth tutorials on **LLMs, RAG, Agents, and more**\\n* Real-world **AI agent** applications\\n* Examples to implement, adapt, and scale in your projects\\n\\nWhether you're a beginner, practitioner, or researcher, this repo provides resources for all skill levels to experiment and succeed in AI engineering.\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 📋 Table of Contents\\n\\n* Getting Started\\n* Newsletter\\n* Projects by Difficulty\\n  \\n    + Beginner Projects (22)\\n    + Intermediate Projects (48)\\n    + Advanced Projects (23)\\n* Contributing\\n* License\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 🎯 Getting Started\\n\\n1. **Complete Beginners** : Check out the AI Engineering Roadmap for a comprehensive learning path\\n2. **Learn the Basics** : Start with Beginner Projects like OCR apps and simple RAG implementations\\n3. **Build Your Skills** : Move to Intermediate Projects with agents and complex workflows\\n4. **Master Advanced Concepts** : Tackle Advanced Projects including fine-tuning and production systems\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 📬 Stay Updated with Our Newsletter!\\n\\n**Get a FREE Data Science eBook** 📖 with 150+ essential lessons in Data Science when you subscribe to our newsletter! Stay in the loop with the latest tutorials, insights, and exclusive resources. [Subscribe now!](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\\n\\n[Daily Dose of Data Science Newsletter](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## 🎓 Projects by Difficulty\\n\\n### 🟢 Beginner Projects\\n\\nPerfect for getting started with AI engineering. These projects focus on single components and straightforward implementations.\\n\\n#### OCR & Vision\\n\\n* **LaTeX OCR with Llama** \\\\- Convert LaTeX equation images to code using Llama 3.2 vision\\n* **Llama OCR** \\\\- 100% local OCR app with Llama 3.2 and Streamlit\\n* **Gemma-3 OCR** \\\\- Local OCR with structured text extraction using Gemma-3\\n* **Qwen 2.5 OCR** \\\\- Text extraction using Qwen 2.5 VL model\\n\\n#### Chat Interfaces & UI\\n\\n* **Local ChatGPT with DeepSeek** \\\\- Mini-ChatGPT with DeepSeek-R1 and Chainlit\\n* **Local ChatGPT with Llama** \\\\- ChatGPT clone using Llama 3.2 vision\\n* **Local ChatGPT with Gemma 3** \\\\- Local chat interface with Gemma 3\\n* **DeepSeek \\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"searchId\": \"search_3b8b9b0b6fea44b1bebebbfaa0305cfc\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"ba169b48-ebce-4e64-a154-af862b034e96\",\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"searchQueries":["AI engineering learning resources tutorials projects 2026 React TypeScript practical applications"],"provider":"parallel-free","count":3,"tookMs":3330,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"parallel-free","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"90e0e3d1d4e23a92\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAI Learning Decoded: The Courses, Repos, and Resources ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"90e0e3d1d4e23a92\">>>","url":"https://tutorialsearch.io/blog/ai-learning-decoded-courses-repos-resources-worth-your-time-2026","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"156c54391ddf1b63\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAI Learning Decoded: The Courses, Repos, and Resources ...\nA curated, honest guide to the best AI learning resources in 2026 — paid courses, free tutorials, GitHub repos, YouTube channels, books, and communities, ranked by someone who actually tested them.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"156c54391ddf1b63\">>>","siteName":"tutorialsearch.io","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b08d5d425e1cd618\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAI Engineering from Scratch\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b08d5d425e1cd618\">>>","url":"https://aiengineeringfromscratch.com/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f50fd97d847ee415\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAI / FROM SCRATCH\n\nContents Catalog Roadmap Glossary About […](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch)\n\nN\n\nFIG\\_000 · curriculum v1.0 · 2026 open source · MIT\n\n# AI Engineering  \nfrom Scratch\n\n503 lessons. 20 phases. Every algorithm built from raw math before a single framework gets imported.\n\nMaintained by Rohit Ghumare and contributors. Run on your own machine.\n\n[Star on GitHub …](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) [Follow @rohitg00](https://github.com/rohitg00)\n\nHow this works\n\nMost AI material teaches in scattered pieces. A paper here, a fine-tuning post there, a flashy agent demo somewhere else. The pieces rarely line up. You ship a chatbot but can't explain its loss curve. You hook a function to an agent but can't say what attention does inside the model that's calling it.\n\nThis curriculum is the spine. 20 phases, 503 lessons, four languages: Python, TypeScript, Rust, Julia. Linear algebra at one end, autonomous swarms at the other. Every algorithm gets built from raw math first. Backprop. Tokenizer. Attention. Agent loop. By the time PyTorch shows up, you already know what it's doing under the hood.\n\nEach lesson runs the same loop: read the problem, derive the math, write the code, run the test, keep the artifact. No five-minute videos, no copy-paste deploys, no hand-holding. Free, open source, and built to run on your own laptop.\n\nCurrent Progress\n\nFinished Lessons bar 0 / 0\n\nPhases bar 0 / 0\n\nLanguages bar 4\n\nGlossary Terms bar ···\n\nCurriculum · 20 phases · 503 lessons\n\nTap a phase to expand its lessons. Each one ships when its math, code, and test are all written.\n\nComplete In progress Planned\n\n×\n\nProgress saved in browser only Reset progress\n\nColophon\n\nThe entire curriculum is on GitHub. Clone it, fork it, learn at your own pace. No paywall, no signup. Every lesson has runnable code in Python, TypeScript, Rust, or Julia, depending on what fits the concept best.\n\n`git clone https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch.git` cp\n\n[GitHub](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch) About Catalog Glossary [Report](https://github.com/rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch/issues/new/choose)\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f50fd97d847ee415\">>>","siteName":"aiengineeringfromscratch.com","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3180cd7f2a1bacdd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - patchy631/ai-engineering-hub: In-depth tutorials on LLMs, RAGs and real-world AI agent applications. · GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3180cd7f2a1bacdd\">>>","url":"https://github.com/patchy631/ai-engineering-hub","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n## Navigation Menu\n\nToggle navigation\n\nAppearance settings\n\nSearch or jump to...\n\n# Search code, repositories, users, issues, pull requests...\n\nAppearance settings\n\nResetting focus\n\npatchy631 / **ai-engineering-hub** Public\n\n* Notifications You must be signed in to change notification settings\n* Fork 5\\.9k\n* Star 35\\.4k\n\n# patchy631/ai-engineering-hub\n\nmain\n\nBranches Tags\n\n \n\nGo to file\n\nCode\n\nOpen more actions menu\n\n## Repository files navigation\n\n* README\n* MIT license\n\n[Trending Badge](https://trendshift.io/repositories/12800)\n\nAI Engineering Hub Banner\n\n* * *\n\n# AI Engineering Hub 🚀\n\nWelcome to the **AI Engineering Hub** \\- your comprehensive resource for learning and building with AI!\n\n## 🌟 Why This Repo?\n\nAI Engineering is advancing rapidly, and staying at the forefront requires both deep understanding and hands-on experience. Here, you will find:\n\n* **93+ Production-Ready Projects** across all skill levels\n* In-depth tutorials on **LLMs, RAG, Agents, and more**\n* Real-world **AI agent** applications\n* Examples to implement, adapt, and scale in your projects\n\nWhether you're a beginner, practitioner, or researcher, this repo provides resources for all skill levels to experiment and succeed in AI engineering.\n\n* * *\n\n## 📋 Table of Contents\n\n* Getting Started\n* Newsletter\n* Projects by Difficulty\n  \n    + Beginner Projects (22)\n    + Intermediate Projects (48)\n    + Advanced Projects (23)\n* Contributing\n* License\n\n* * *\n\n## 🎯 Getting Started\n\n1. **Complete Beginners** : Check out the AI Engineering Roadmap for a comprehensive learning path\n2. **Learn the Basics** : Start with Beginner Projects like OCR apps and simple RAG implementations\n3. **Build Your Skills** : Move to Intermediate Projects with agents and complex workflows\n4. **Master Advanced Concepts** : Tackle Advanced Projects including fine-tuning and production systems\n\n* * *\n\n## 📬 Stay Updated with Our Newsletter!\n\n**Get a FREE Data Science eBook** 📖 with 150+ essential lessons in Data Science when you subscribe to our newsletter! Stay in the loop with the latest tutorials, insights, and exclusive resources. [Subscribe now!](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\n\n[Daily Dose of Data Science Newsletter](https://join.dailydoseofds.com)\n\n* * *\n\n## 🎓 Projects by Difficulty\n\n### 🟢 Beginner Projects\n\nPerfect for getting started with AI engineering. These projects focus on single components and straightforward implementations.\n\n#### OCR & Vision\n\n* **LaTeX OCR with Llama** \\- Convert LaTeX equation images to code using Llama 3.2 vision\n* **Llama OCR** \\- 100% local OCR app with Llama 3.2 and Streamlit\n* **Gemma-3 OCR** \\- Local OCR with structured text extraction using Gemma-3\n* **Qwen 2.5 OCR** \\- Text extraction using Qwen 2.5 VL model\n\n#### Chat Interfaces & UI\n\n* **Local ChatGPT with DeepSeek** \\- Mini-ChatGPT with DeepSeek-R1 and Chainlit\n* **Local ChatGPT with Llama** \\- ChatGPT clone using Llama 3.2 vision\n* **Local ChatGPT with Gemma 3** \\- Local chat interface with Gemma 3\n* **DeepSeek \n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9bb5410c9ff1c656\">>>","siteName":"github.com","excerpts":{"truncated":true,"reason":"trajectory-depth-limit","limitDepth":6}}],"searchId":"search_3b8b9b0b6fea44b1bebebbfaa0305cfc","sessionId":"ba169b48-ebce-4e64-a154-af862b034e96","usage":[{"name":"sku_search","count":1}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781712140096},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora crearé el reporte matutino especializado:\n\n# 📊 REPORTE MATUTINO - IA ENGINEERING PARA KENNETH\n**Fecha: 17 de junio, 2026** ⏰ **Hora UTC: 16:00** (Hora Costa Rica: ~10:00 AM)\n\n---\n\n## 🌤️ **1. TEMPERATURA GOICOECHEA, CR**\n**Actual:** 24°C (sensación 25°C) - Nublado  \n**Humedad:** 65% | **Viento:** 8 km/h  \n**Previsión del día:** Máx. 25°C | Mín. 19°C | Prob. lluvia: 94% 🌧️  \n**Condición:** Tiempo templado con lluvias por la tarde - típico del Valle Central.\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 **2. NOTICIAS TÉCNICAS PARA IA ENGINEERS**\n\n### **FRAMEWORKS TYPE/JS PARA 2026**\nLos frameworks TypeScript para IA están redefiniendo el desarrollo full-stack:\n\n**🔹 Top 5 Frameworks comparados:**\n1. **Genkit** (Google) - Flows tipados, UI dev, neutralidad de proveedores\n2. **Vercel AI SDK** - Generación estructurada, patrones de agentes  \n3. **Mastra** - Workflows, excelente para frontend/backend unificado\n4. **LangChain** - Agentes-first, observabilidad con LangSmith\n5. **Google ADK** - Sistemas multi-agente, enfoque enterprise\n\n**🔹 Capas de Frameworks TypeScript:**\n- **Loop:** Mastra, Vercel AI SDK, Claude Agent SDK\n- **Runtime:** Mastra Platform, LangGraph Platform, Inngest  \n- **Sandbox:** Ejecución aislada de agentes coding en paralelo\n\n---\n\n### **INTEGRACIÓN FRONTEND + IA**\n**Tendencias clave 2026:**\n- **AI-first workflows** en meta-frameworks\n- **Edge computing** para inferencia rápida\n- **TypeScript** como lenguaje unificado (frontend + backend + IA)\n- **Arquitectura moderna** con React/Next.js + TypeScript SDKs\n\n**🔧 Herramientas accesibles:**\n- `@ai-sdk/react` - Hooks React para modelos de IA\n- `@vercel/ai` - SDK Vercel para streaming UI\n- `@google/genkit` - UI dev y testing local\n- **Tailwind + AI SDKs** - Diseño moderno + funcionalidad IA\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ **3. ANÁLISIS PRÁCTICO: CÓMO APLICAR**\n\n### **PROYECTO DE APRENDIZAJE #1: Chat UI Local**\n**Stack recomendado:** React + Vercel AI SDK + Tailwind\n```bash\nnpx create-next-app@latest my-ai-chat --typescript\nnpm install ai @ai-sdk/react @vercel/ai\n```\n**Objetivo:** Chat local con DeepSeek/Claude, streaming UI, historial.\n\n### **PROYECTO #2: Agente RAG Básico**\n**Stack:** Next.js + Mastra + PostgreSQL/pgvector\n- Extraer documentos PDF\n- Embeddings con `@ai-sdk/provider-openai`\n- Búsqueda semántica + contexto\n- UI tipo ChatGPT para consultas\n\n### **PROYECTO #3: Dashboard con Insights IA**\n**Stack:** Vue 3 + TypeScript + Genkit\n- Visualización de datos + análisis IA\n- Generación automática de reportes\n- Integración con APIs externas\n\n---\n\n## 📚 **4. RECOMENDACIÓN DIARIA**\n\n### **🎯 RECURSO DEL DÍA: AI Engineering from Scratch**\n**GitHub:** `rohitg00/ai-engineering-from-scratch`\n- **503 lecciones** en 20 fases\n- **4 lenguajes:** Python, TypeScript, Rust, Julia\n- **Enfoque:** Matemáticas primero → implementación\n- **Perfecto para:** Fundamentos sólidos antes de frameworks\n\n### **🛠️ TUTORIAL PRÁCTICO:**\n**\"Build a Local AI Assistant with React & Mastra\"**\n**Pasos:**\n1. Setup Mastra con TypeScript\n2. Configurar modelo local (Ollama/DeepSeek)\n3. Crear componentes React con streaming\n4. Agregar memory/session management\n5. Deploy en Vercel/Netlify\n\n**Tiempo estimado:** 2-3 horas\n**Nivel:** Intermedio\n**Skills adquiridos:** TypeScript, React hooks, AI SDKs, deployment\n\n---\n\n## 💡 **CONSEJO DEL DÍA**\n**\"Empieza pequeño, escala gradualmente\"**\n- Semana 1: Chat básico con streaming\n- Semana 2: Agente simple con herramientas  \n- Semana 3: RAG con embeddings\n- Semana 4: Sistema multi-agente\n\nLos frameworks TypeScript permiten **iteración rápida** - prueba Genkit para UI dev o Mastra para workflows complejos.\n\n---\n\n**🔗 Recursos adicionales:**\n- `github.com/patchy631/ai-engineering-hub` (93+ proyectos)\n- `tutorialsearch.io/blog/ai-learning-decoded` (cursos 2026)\n- `dev.to/tags/ai` (tutoriales prácticos)\n\n---\n\n¿Te gustaría profundizar en algún framework específico o proyecto práctico? 🎯\n\n**¡Feliz coding!** 👨‍💻🔥"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781712140115,"responseId":"gen-1781712140-Kk42FeVv5ZZ45DfSdZCz"}]}}
